# Agent Orchestration

Governing rules (from `.cursor/references/orchestration-patterns.md`):

1. **User or slash-command is the orchestrator.** Personas do not call personas.
2. **Only one endorsed fan-out pattern:** parallel independent reports → merge in main agent (`/afenda-ship`).
3. **Sequential lifecycle** stays user-driven — no LLM lifecycle orchestrator.
4. **Never build:** meta-router persona, persona-chains, deep persona trees, sequential paraphrasing orchestrator.

## Decision matrix

```
One perspective on one artifact?
├── Yes → Direct persona or /afenda-review
└── No  → Will it repeat?
         ├── No  → Ad hoc direct invocation
         └── Yes → Independent sub-tasks?
                  ├── No  → User runs commands in sequence (spec → plan → build → test → review → ship)
                  └── Yes → /afenda-ship parallel fan-out + merge
```

| Task | Entry |
| --- | --- |
| Skill discovery | [`using-afenda-skills`](.cursor/skills/using-afenda-skills/SKILL.md) |
| Pre-merge review (single) | `/afenda-review` |
| Ship / go-no-go | `/afenda-ship` |
| PAS parallel batch | `@afenda-orchestrator` + [`afenda-batch`](.cursor/skills/afenda-batch/SKILL.md) |
| Code edit | `coding-consistency-bundle` (implementers only) |

## Cursor mapping

Parallel fan-out = **multiple Task tool calls in one assistant turn** with `readonly: true` subagents.

Review personas skip bundle preflight — hooks scope edit tools to implementers.

